## Auth + routing

Three layers must agree:

1. `middleware`-style server checks live in the FastAPI backend.
2. [`AuthGuard`](src/auth/AuthGuard.tsx) redirects unauthenticated users to `/login`.
3. [`RoleGuard`](src/auth/RoleGuard.tsx) hard-codes per-role path allowlists. **If you add a dashboard route, update the staff allowlist here AND, if admin-only, the `role === 'admin'` block in `Sidebar.tsx`.** Forgetting either causes silent redirects or invisible nav items.

## Deploy to Vercel

[`vercel.json`](vercel.json) pins the build command (`vite build`), output dir (`dist`), and the SPA fallback rewrite that sends every unknown path to `/index.html` so `react-router-dom` deep links survive a hard refresh.

### One-time setup

1. Sign in to https://vercel.com with GitHub.
2. **Add New… → Project** → import `super-dev-vibe/engineersapp`.
3. Vercel auto-detects Vite. Confirm: Build = `npm run build`, Output = `dist`.
4. Under **Environment Variables**, add:

| Name | Example value | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `VITE_API_BASE_URL` | `https://engineers-backend.onrender.com` | Your live FastAPI host. Include scheme, no trailing slash. **Read at build time**, so changing it requires a redeploy, not a config flip. |

5. **Deploy**.

### CORS — both ends must agree

After Vercel assigns the URL (e.g. `https://engineersapp-xyz.vercel.app`), set it as `FRONTEND_ORIGIN` on the backend (Render env var) and let the backend redeploy. Without this the browser will block every request with a CORS error.

```
Order of operations:
  deploy backend → grab Vercel URL → set FRONTEND_ORIGIN on backend → redeploy backend → deploy SPA
```

`FRONTEND_ORIGIN` must match scheme + host + port exactly. No trailing slash.

### Free-tier limits worth knowing

| Limit | What it means |
|---|---|
| **100 GB bandwidth / month** | A SPA + API calls won't come close. |
| **6000 build minutes / month** | A push burns ~3 min. |
| **Vercel doesn't host the API** | Backend lives on Render (or anywhere FastAPI runs). Vercel only serves the static bundle. |

